.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33CB651CFFB9FFF95BE9FF7DE2ECFEED" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7B6E3697FFB9FFF95BE9FF7DE2ECFEED" blockId="24.[192,1440,195,284]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFB9FFF95BE9FF7DE502FF2D" bold="true" box="[240,590,195,219]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis and discussion.</emphasis>
A bright tawny and completely unmarked species, 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFB9FFF95FABFF7AE21AFF2D" authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[1202,1366,195,219]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFB9FFF95FABFF7AE21AFF2D" box="[1202,1366,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">P. splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the largest of the known 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFB9FFF9590EFF5DE580FF0D" box="[535,716,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFB9FFF9590EFF5DE580FF0D" box="[535,716,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Porphyrogenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comparable in size to 
<taxonomicName id="BCD14D14FFB9FFF958F2FF5AE32DFF0D" authorityName="Moschler" authorityYear="1877" box="[1003,1121,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Telegonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="probus">
<emphasis id="49A5EA85FFB9FFF958F2FF5AE32DFF0D" box="[1003,1121,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">P. probus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It appears unique in the genus by having asymmetrical valvae. It resembles the species to be described next (see discussion there).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
